2058bb31-8434-4d0c-ad15-6cb65335adc4.024a2aa2-731f-49e2-82cc-af5866bd4bc2.prompt=HostName\: 2058bb31-8434-4d0c-ad15-6cb65335adc4.12724df3-2060-4b0a-8db1-4fbf2ccf9674.prompt=HostName\: 2058bb31-8434-4d0c-ad15-6cb65335adc4.3b4370cb-b3b4-4b68-9c71-e7e31ab8b0be.prompt=Password\: 2058bb31-8434-4d0c-ad15-6cb65335adc4.715f5585-8b3e-43e0-9554-cd002d50a08e.description=
Runs multiple SSH command by creating an ssh shell and checking output against regular expressions

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
port - the port number for running the command. It overwrites the port given inside the host input -in a syntax like host\:port-, if this exists.
command - the commands to execute. This should be made up of 'send ' and 'expect ' statements separated be newlines.
username - username to connect as
password - password
privateKeyFile - private key to be used during ssh authentication.
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete
newlineCharacters - The character sequence to send as the enter key being pressed after each 'send' statement in a send expect script is processed. Either '\r\n' '\n' '\r' or a comma delimited list of ASCII escape sequences.
characterDelay - the delay in milliseconds between sending characters of the SSH commands. 

Responses\:
success - the command was executed successfully
failure - the command could not be executed

Extra Results\:
visualized - the output of the command in XML format
STDOUT - the STDOUT of the command

2058bb31-8434-4d0c-ad15-6cb65335adc4.942ac53c-3fe1-4fec-9d0b-368d1edf5c9d.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.
